<h1>THERE ARE NO CHILDREN HERE<br>
<i></i></h1>
 
<table cellpadding=10 width=90%>
 
<tr valign=top>
 
<td align=center>
<img src="/10000086.gif">
 
<br><p>Nonfiction<br>
ISBN: 1-879371-15-4<br>
Abridged<br>2 tapes, 180 min.<br>
$15.95
 
</td><td>
 
 
<h3>By Alex Kotlowitz<br>
Read by Whoopi Goldberg</h3>
<P>
<p>This is that rare kind of book which holds the power to change lives.  In the spirit of James Agee, Alex
Kotlowitz brings to our attention a side of America we perhaps would not otherwise know, exploring
America's embattled inner cities through the lives of two remarkable young boys.

<p>Lafayette and Pharoah Rivers live in Chicago's Henry Horner Homes, a public housing complex disfigured
by crime and neglect.  Here, in the bleak heart of the other America, they fight the odds, growing up where
growing up is an achievement.


 
