<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Publishing Mills Audiobooks - TIDES OF MAINE (THE),  Smithsonian Institution</TITLE>
</HEAD>
 
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<FORM METHOD="post" ACTION="/cgi-shl/html_web_store.pl">
 
<img src="/pmhead2.gif" align=right>
<HR noshade>
 
<P>
<center>
<h1>TIDES OF MAINE (THE)<br>
<i>A radio documentary of the Smithsonian Institution and Soundprint</i></h1>
 
<table cellpadding=10 width=90%>
 
<tr valign=top>
 
<td align=center>
<img src="/10000008.gif">
 
<br><p>Nonfiction<br>
ISBN: 1-57511-009-1<br>
Original Work<br>1 tape, 27 min.<br>
$10.95
 
</td><td>
 
 
<h3>By  Smithsonian Institution<br>
Read by Walter Adey</h3>
<P>
<p>        Tides of Maine is an actual "live" recording of a
ship's log during a voyage from Norfolk, Virginia to
the Gulf of Maine with Smithsonian Institute marine
biologist Walter Adey and his crew.  This audio documentary
records life aboard the 55 - foot sailing ship
and charts Adey's stories as a seafaring scientist.
Adey, who has spent a lifetime studying the ecosystem
of the Gulf, leads the listener on a journey which
tracks and explains specimens of the plant and
animal life along the route of the excursion.
TIDES OF MAINE is a story about one man's lifetime
of passionate curiosity about how ocean life works
and our part in this process.



 
