<h1>VIRGINIAN (THE)<br>
<i></i></h1>
 
<table cellpadding=10 width=90%>
 
<tr valign=top>
 
<td align=center>
<img src="/10000071.gif">
 
<br><p>Westerns<br>
ISBN: 1-879371-48-0<br>
Abridged<br>2 tapes, 180 min.<br>
$16.95
 
</td><td>
 
 
<h3>By Owen Wister<br>
Read by Patrick Duffy</h3>
<P>
<p>Dime novels had featured some rather scrawny horse-bound tenders of cattle, but not until 1902 did the
cowboy become a fully realized article of American culture.  An immediate bestseller, <b><I>The Virginian</I></b> never
faded from public consciousness it paved the way for generations of readers and movie-goers as to what they
now expect from a western.  To listen to <b><I>The Virginian</I></b> is to approach the beginning of a cultural
phenomenon.



 
