<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Institute of Physical Resource Theory -- Research</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Institute of Physical Resource Theory -- Research</H2>
At the Institute of Physical Resource Theory the physical criteria for sustainable
use of natural resources in society are examined on a local, national and
global level.. Economic theory and economic analysis of the use of natural
resources is also carried out at the institute. Studies within the field
of technology and global security are also carried out at the institute
with a special interest given to nuclear non-proliferation. The scientific
basis of the institute's research is in physics where the institute does
research within the areas of thermodynamics, information theory and complex
systems.<BR>
<BR>
<HR>Move back to the <A HREF="frteng.html">institute's home page</A>.<BR>
