<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Institute of Physical Resource Theory --Teaching</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Institute of Physical Resource Theory -- Teaching</H2>
At the institute teaching is carried out mainly at the School of Engineering
Physics at Chalmers, but some courses are also held for the university at
large. The responsibility for planning and administrating for courses in
Man-Technology-Society at Chalmers is based at the institute. Graduate studies
in physical resourse theory as well as in environmental technology and science
can be followed at the institute.<BR>
<BR>
The following undergraduate courses are given by the institute (1 unit =
1 week's studies) : 
<UL>
  <LI>Natural Resources and Society, 3 units 
  <LI>Applied Resource Theory, 3 units 
  <LI>Energy Physics, 3 units 
  <LI>Technology and Global Security, 3 units 
  <LI>Information Theory for Complex Systems, 3 units 
</UL>
In addition the institute is to give a lecture series on &quot;Technology
and Global Security&quot; during the fall of 1996.<BR>
<BR>
