<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Challenges of Sustainable Development (Conference)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H1><CENTER><I>CHALLENGES OF<BR>
SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT</I></CENTER>
</H1>
<H3><CENTER><BR>
Amsterdam, 22-25 August 1996<BR>
<BR>
The Netherlands</CENTER>
</H3>
<H1><CENTER><BR>
International Congress of<BR>
Engineers and Scientists<BR>
<HR></CENTER>
</H1>
<H3><CENTER><BR>
<A HREF="amst/report.html">Here is Hartwig Spitzer's report from the Congress.</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG><A HREF="amst/appeal.html">TOWARDS SUSTAINABLE SOCIETIES<BR>
- An Appeal to Engineers and Scientists -</A></STRONG><BR>
<BR>
The Congress will in parts be documented on these pages. Abstracts for some
of the <A HREF="#anchor395874">workshop</A> and <A HREF="#anchor198587">poster
session</A> papers can already be found on these pages.</CENTER>
</H3>
<HR><STRONG>The congress addressed scientists and engineers as well as policy-makers,
development and environmental experts, and economic practitioners. In plenary
sessions, speakers from a wide range of countries will discuss problems
of global sustainability. In addition, there are be twenty parallel workshop
meetings, where the ethical, economic, technical, political and security
dimensions of sustainability are treated in detail. The goal of the congress
is to clarify the possibilities of, and the obstacles to, achieving sustainability
of development in all parts of the world.</STRONG> <BR>
<P><CENTER><HR>Organized by the <BR>
<STRONG><A HREF="http://www.mindspring.com/~us016262/ines.html">International
Network of Engineers and Scientists for Global Responsibility (INES)</A></STRONG>,<BR>
in cooperation with<BR>
the <STRONG><A HREF="http://www.uva.nl/english.html">University of Amsterdam</A></STRONG>,<BR>
the <STRONG><A HREF="http://www.xs4all.nl/~foeint/wupper.html">Wuppertal
Institute for Climate, Environment and Energy</A></STRONG> <BR>
and the <A HREF="http://www.fiet.org/fiet/"><B><STRONG>International Federation
of Commercial, Clerical, Professional and Technical </STRONG></B><STRONG>Employees
(FIET)</STRONG></A>.<BR>
<BR>
<HR><STRONG>The Conference Secretariat</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
Mr. Reiner Braun (Executive Secretary), <BR>
Gutenbergstr. 31, 44139 Dortmund, Germany <BR>
TEL: +49 231 575 202, FAX: +49 231 575 210, <BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:r.braun@ping.de">r.braun@ping.de </A></CENTER>
