<BODY>
<H1><CENTER>Johan A. Swahn</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><B><BR>
Assistant professor (Physical Resource Theory/Technology and Global Security)<BR>
Ph.D. (Technical Peace Research)<BR>
M.Sc. (Engineering Physics)</B><BR>
Go to my <A HREF="johanswe.html">Swedish Home Page</A>. <BR>
<BR>
<HR><A HREF="johanbild.html">THIS IS WHAT I LOOK LIKE!</A> (39k)<BR>
<HR><B>Work</B></CENTER>
<P>Institute of Physical Resource Theory<BR>
Chalmers University of Technology and G&ouml;teborg University<BR>
G&ouml;teborg (Gothenburg), Sweden<BR>
<BR>
Mailing Address:<BR>
Physical Resource Theory<BR>
Chalmers Inst. of Technology<BR>
S-412 96 G&ouml;teborg, Sweden<BR>
<BR>
E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:frtjs@fy.chalmers.se">frtjs@fy.chalmers.se</A><BR>
Tel: +46 31 772 31 30<BR>
Fax: +46 31 772 31 50<BR>
<BR>
At the institute I work mainly within the field of Technology and Global
Security, foremost with nuclear non-proliferation issues, most notably long-term
safeguard problems with geologic repositories for spent fuel.<BR>
<BR>
Some of my research time is spent on a project together with collegues at
the Institute to develop scenarios for sustainable energy futures.<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="johanpubl.html">Here is a list of publications</A>.<BR>
<P><CENTER><HR><B>Home/Family</B></CENTER>
<P>Bj&ouml;rkek&auml;rrsgatan 2<BR>
S-416 80 G&ouml;teborg (Gothenburg), Sweden<BR>
<BR>
Tel: +46 31 19 82 48<BR>
<BR>
Married to <A HREF="mailto:eva.eiderstrom@snf.se">Eva Eiderstr&ouml;m</A>
who is Campaign Coordinator for the Shop and Act Green Campaign at the <A HREF="http://www.snf.se/">Swedish
Society for Nature Conservation (only in Swedish)</A>.<BR>
<BR>
We have three boys, Linus (8 years), Hampus (5 years) and Rasmus (&lt;1
year).<BR>
