<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Press Conference and Media Event</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>PRESS CONFERENCE AND MEDIA EVENT</H2>
<BR>
<STRONG>Press Conference:</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
On Thursday, August 22, 14.00 hours, there will be a press-conference<BR>
(location: Auditorium UvA, Singel 411, on the corner Singel/Spui), with
the<BR>
following persons. The chairpersons of the programme committee: prof.<BR>
Philip Smith (University of Groningen, Pugwash The Netherlands) and prof<BR>
Valery Petrosyan (Lomonosov University, adviser of the Duma for<BR>
environmental problems). Other member of the press-forum will be: prof.
dr.<BR>
Spitzer (University of Hamburg), prof Devaki Jain (Vice-President of the<BR>
Women's Conference in Beijing and now on the Executive Board of the ongoing<BR>
process of the Women's Conference) and prof Anne Maria Cetto (Universidad<BR>
Nacional Aut&oacute;noma de M&eacute;xico). They will further explain the
goal of the<BR>
conference and answer questions. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Media event:</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
Sustainable development has a scientific and a societal component. Therefore<BR>
we approach all media: the professional and more generally orientated press,<BR>
on a local, regional, national and international scale.<BR>
Besides the scientific congress we also will have some media events, like
a<BR>
bicycle tour from Dortmund to Amsterdam and the planting of a tree in the<BR>
Bulderbos as a form 'of CO2 compensation' for all the necessary<BR>
travelling. The Bulderbos is a small piece of land bought up by some<BR>
environmental groups in order to prevent the enlargement of Schiphol, so
the<BR>
planting is a political gesture. <BR>
<BR>
Time and place: Saturday 24, 15.00 hours in the Bulderbos. <BR>
<BR>
For information about transport ask Armin Tenner (<A HREF="mailto:q18@nikhef.nl">q18@nikhef.nl</A>)<BR>
<BR>
<HR>Go back to the <A HREF="schedule.html">schedule page</A>.<BR>
<BR>
Go back to the <A HREF="../amsterdam#anchor144689">main page</A>.<BR>
