<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Poster and Video Session</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>POSTER AND VIDEO SESSION<BR>
</H2>
<H3><HR><BR>
<A HREF="posterabstracts.html">Abstracts for poster session</A></H3>
<BR>
<HR><BR>
Coordinators: <BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="mailto:lars.ryden@uadm.uu.se">Lars Ryd&eacute;n</A> (Sweden) and
<A HREF="mailto:ines@sara.nl">Armin Tenner</A> (Netherlands)<BR>
<BR>
The Interactive Poster Session will be held on 24 August after the conclusion
of the workshops. The session serves a threefold purpose: <BR>
<BR>
1. Presentation of key findings and conclusions of the workshops (statements
<BR>
of fact, intention and implementation). Participants will have the opportunity
of inquiring about the work and results of other workshops. <BR>
<BR>
2. Presentation of the objectives and work of INES member organizations
<BR>
and projects and of organizations which support the congress. <BR>
<BR>
3. Presentation and discussion of conceptual work and practical steps towards
<BR>
sustainable development by congress participants. <BR>
<BR>
The presentation will be based on poster displays. Supplementary display
of short video presentations is also being considered. Authors of posters
are under obligation to be available for questions during the full duration
of the poster session.<BR>
<BR>
<HR>Go back to the <A HREF="../amsterdam#anchor198587">main page</A>.<BR>
