<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Visa applications</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>VISA APPLICATIONS</H2>
For citizens of various countries a visa is needed for being admitted to
the Netherlands. Visa requests should be made at a Dutch embassy or consulate
in your own country, at least three months before the beginning of the journey.
For preference, applicants should show a letter of invitation to the congress.
If you do not have such a letter, please ask the Conference Secretariat
to provide it. No visa is needed if you already have a visa for the proper
period for one of the countries of the Schengen group.<BR>
<BR>
