    <TITLE>INES Congress: ftp archive</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>CONGRESS FTP ARCHIVE</H2>
<BR>
Here files can be retrieved for reading and printing off-line. These files
can be text files, Acrobat Reader (pdf) files or postscript files.<BR>
<BR>
You may also use other software that can fetch files using the ftp protocol
and long in as an anonomous user (User: anonomous, Password: your e-mail
address) at the site ftp.frt.fy.chalmers.se. The files are found in the
/Pub/INES folder. 
<H4><HR><IMG SRC="../images/pdf.gif" WIDTH="32" HEIGHT="32" ALIGN="BOTTOM"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">PDF FILES</H4>
<BR>
The Acrobat reader format is readable and printable on many platforms (Windows,
DOS, Macintosh, several UNIX Workstations) if you have installed Acrobat
Reader. Many Congress documents will in the final form be produced in the
pdf format, so you may find it worthwhile to explore this.<BR>
<BR>
Use this link to download <A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/Software/Acrobat/">free
Acrobat Reader software from Adobe</A> in order to be able to read and print
the pdf files.<A HREF="http://www.adobe.com/acrobat/"><BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="../images/GetAcro.gif" WIDTH="90" HEIGHT="31" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"0" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A><BR>
<BR>
If you use Netscape as a web browser, <A HREF="netscape.html">here is information</A>
on how to configure the application for use with Acrobat reader.<BR>
<BR>
<HR>The following files are presently available in the archives: <BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>SCEDULES PROGRAMMES ETC</STRONG> 
<PRE>Name:schedule.txt            Description: Congress schedule
