1.	K. Lindgren and B. &Aring;. M&aring;nsson, "Entropy production in a chaotic 
chemical system", <i>Zeitschrift f&uuml;r Naturforschung</i> <b>41a</b>, 
1111-1117 (1986).<p>
2.	K.-E. Eriksson and K. Lindgren, "Structural information in self-organizing 
systems," <i>Physica Scipta </i><b>35</b>, 388-397 (1987).<p>
3.	K. Lindgren, "Correlations and random information in cellular automata",
<i>Complex Systems</i> <b>1</b>, 529-543 (1987).<p>
4.	K.-E. Eriksson, K. Lindgren, and B. &Aring;. M&aring;nsson, <i>Structure, 
Context, Complexity, and Organization</i> (World Scientific, Singapore, 
1987).<p>
5.	K. Lindgren and M. G. Nordahl, "Complexity measures and cellular automata",
<i>Complex Systems</i> <b>2</b>, 409-440 (1988).<p>
6.	K. Lindgren, "Microscopic and macroscopic entropy", <i>Physical Review
</i><b>A38</b>, 4794-4798 (1988).<p>
7.	K. Lindgren, <i>Physics and Information Theory</i> (doctoral thesis, 
Chalmers University of Technology , G&ouml;teborg, 1988).<p>
8.	K.-E. Eriksson and K. Lindgren, "Entropy and correlations in lattice 
systems", Inst. of Physical Resource Theory, report 89-1 (1989).<p>
9.	K. Lindgren, "Entropy and correlations in dynamical lattice systems", pp. 
27-40 in P. Manneville, N. Boccara, G. Y. Vichniac, and R. Bidaux (eds.),
<i>Cellular Automata and Modelling of Complex Physical Systems</i> (Springer, 
Berlin, 1989).<p>
10.	K. Lindgren and M. G. Nordahl, "Universal computation in simple 
one-dimensional cellular automata", <i>Complex Systems</i> <b>4</b>, 299-318 
(1990).<p>
11.	K. Lindgren, "Entropy and correlations in discrete dynamical systems", pp. 
88-109 i <i>Beyond Belief: Randomness, Prediction and Explanation in 
Science</i>, J. L. Casti and A. Karlqvist (eds.), (CRC Press, Boca Raton, 
Florida, 1991).<p>
12.	B.&Aring;. M&aring;nsson and K. Lindgren, "Thermodynamics, information, and 
structure", in <i>Advances in Thermodynamics, Vol. 3: Nonequilibrium Theory and 
Extremum Principles</i>, S. Sieniutycz and P. Salamon (eds.), (Taylor and 
Francis, New York, 1991).<p>
13.	K. Lindgren, "Evolutionary phenomena in simple dynamics", pp. 295-312 in
<i>Artificial Life II</i>, C. Langton et al (eds.), (Addison-Wesley, Redwood 
City, 1991).<p>
14.	K. Lindgren, A. Nilsson, M. G. Nordahl, and I. R&aring;de, "Regular 
language inference using evolving recurrent neural networks", pp. 75-86 in
<i>COGANN-92 International Workshop on Combinations of Genetic Algorithms and 
Neural Networks</i>, L. D. Whitley and J. D. Schaffer (eds.) (IEEE Computer 
Society Press, Los Alamitos, CA, 1992).<p>
15.	K. Lindgren, "Universal computation and undecidability in cellular 
automata", pp. 108-119 i <i>Theory and Control of Dynamical Systems</i>, S. I. 
Andersson et al (eds.), (World Scientific, Singapore, 1992).<p>
16.	K. Lindgren, "Evolution in a population of mutating strategies", pp. 95-107 
in <i>Theory and Control of Dynamical Systems</i>, S. I. Andersson et al 
(eds.), (World Scientific, Singapore, 1992).<p>
17.	K. Lindgren och M. G. Nordahl, "Helt komplext men delvis enkelt", pp. 61-85 
in Kosmos 1992, (Swedish Science Press, 1992). (In Swedish.)<p>
18.	K. Lindgren, A. Nilsson, M. G. Nordahl, and I. R&aring;de, "Evolving 
recurrent neural networks", pp. 55-62 in <i>Artificial Neural Nets and Genetic 
Algorithms</i>, Albrecht et al (1993).<p>
19.	K. Lindgren and M. G. Nordahl, "Artificial food webs", <i>Artificial Life 
III</i>, C. Langton (ed.), (Addison-Wesley, 1993).<p>
20.	K. Lindgren and M. G. Nordahl, "Evolutionary dynamics of spatial games",
<i>Physica </i><b>D 75</b>, 292-309 (1994).<p>
21.	K. Lindgren and M. G. Nordahl, "Cooperation and community structure in 
artificial ecosystems", <i>Artificial Life</i> <b>1</b>, 15-39 (1994).<p>
22.	S. Karlsson, C. Azar, K.-E. Eriksson, J. Holmberg, K. Lindgren, and S. 
Wirsenius, "Material flows: On the metabolism of the industrial society in a 
sustainability perspective", AFR-report 38, Swedish Waste Research Council 
(1994).<p>
23.	C. Azar, J. Holmberg, and K. Lindgren, "Stability analysis of harvesting in 
a predator-prey model", <i>Journal of Theoretical Biology</i> (1995).<p>
24.	C. Azar, J. Holmberg, and K. Lindgren, "Socio-ecological indicators for 
sustainability", preprint 1995:01 (1995).<p>
25.	C. Azar, K. Lindgren, and J. Holmberg, "Constant quota versus constant 
effort harvesting", preprint 1995:07, accepted for publication in
<i>Environmental and Resource Economics</i> (1995).<p>
