    <TITLE>INES Congress:Suggested preparatory reading</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>PREPARATORY READING SUGGESTED BY THE CONGRESS ORGANIZERS</H2>
<BR>
In the following we mention several documents, books and studies which illustrate
different approaches towards and conceptual studies of sustainable development.
You are welcome to suggest additional texts for inclusion in this list by
sending e-mail to Hartwig Spitzer, INES Chairman at <A HREF="mailto:f36hue@dsyibm.desy.de">f36hue@dsyibm.desy.de</A>)
who prepared this list.<BR>
<BR>
Please note that many studies focus on the economic and environmental/ecological
aspoects of sustainable development. The Congress organizers believe that
social and cultural aspects (justice, peace-.keeping, cultural diversity,
spiritual and ethical basis) have to be covered and developed as well.<BR>
<BR>
a) Early texts<BR>
<BR>
Our Common Future, World Commission on Environment and Development (&quot;The
Brundtland Commission&quot;). Oxford University Press 1987.<BR>
<BR>
b) United Nations documents<BR>
<BR>
Agenda 21 and other material from the <A HREF="gopher://gopher.undp.org/1/unconfs/UNCED">United
Nations Conference on Environment and Development (UNCED)</A> - &quot;The
1992 Rio Conference&quot;.<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="gopher://gopher.undp.org/1/ungophers/popin/icpd">International
Conference on Population and Development (ICPD)</A> in Cairo, 1994.<BR>
<BR>
United Nations <A HREF="http://www.undp.org/wssd/wssd.html">World Summit
for Social Development</A> in Copenhagen, 1995.<BR>
<BR>
United Nations <A HREF="http://www.undp.org/fwcw/daw1.htm">Fourth World
Conference on Women</A> in Beijing, 1995.<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.undp.org/un/habitat/">Habitat II - Second United Nations
Conference on Human Settlements</A> in Istambul, 1996.<BR>
<BR>
c) Recent conceptual studies for regional development<BR>
<BR>
Action Plan Sustainable Netherlands. Milieudefensie, Friends of the Earth
Netherlands, 1992.<BR>
<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.xs4all.nl/~foeint/suseur.html">Towards Sustainable Europe</A>,
1995.<BR>
<BR>
The Netherlands and the World Ecology. The Netherlands Committee for IUCN,
1994<BR>
<BR>
<TT>The Netherlands Committee for IUCN, Plantaage Middenlaan 2B,<BR>
NL-1018 DD Amsterdam, Netherlands, fax: +31 20 6279349.<BR>
</TT><BR>
Zukunftsf&auml;higes Deutchland (<A HREF="http://www.xs4all.nl/~foeint/content.html">Sustainable
Germany</A>), BUND/Misereor (eds), Birkh&auml;user Verlag1996 . <BR>
<BR>
<TT>Basel/Berlin: Birkhaeuser Verlag (E-mail:graf@birkhauser.ch), <BR>
Klosterberg 23, CH-4010 Basel, <BR>
Tel.+41 61- 050707, Fax +41 61 2050792<BR>
or<BR>
BUND (Friends of the Earth Germany), PO Box 300251,<BR>
D-53182 Bonn, Germany,<BR>
Tel. +49 228 400970, Fax +49 228 4009740.<BR>
<BR>
</TT>d) Holistic View of Sustainable Development<BR>
<BR>
The World at the Crossroads - Towards a Sustainable, Equitable and Livable
World. Philip Smith et al. eds., Earthscan 1994.<BR>
<BR>
<TT>Earthscan Publications Ltd., 120 Pentonville Rd, London N1 9JN, <BR>
United Kingdom<BR>
Tel: 44 71 2780433<BR>
Fax: 44 71 2781142<BR>
