<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Case studies</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>3.3 Case studies of successfull development through sustainability</H2>
<BR>
<STRONG>Convenor: <BR>
</STRONG><BR>
Wolf Dieter Grossmann, Director <BR>
Umweltforschungszentrum Leipzig <BR>
Permoserstr. 15, 04318 Leipzig, Deutschland<BR>
TEL: +49 341 235 2282, FAX: +49 341 235 2511 <BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:wdgross@alok.ufz.de">wdgross@alok.ufz.de </A><BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Topic: <BR>
</STRONG><BR>
Already now most people are living in urban conglomerations. This workshop
will cover the synergy of the development of a future-oriented economy,
the shaping of a viable landscape and the encouragement of people and creativity.
The objective is the initiation of new thinking and positive development.
Information-rich economies and lifestyles will act as catalysts.<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Workshop description:</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
The workshop is based on our experiences from case studies. We sit down
with people and elaborate together with them, given their present business
and job, lifestyle and whatever, how they can use the new possibilities
of the Information Society. Afterwards we begin together to outline the
new, resulting, options for a different land use, different landscape design,
different traffic, different traffic infrastructure etc. In this process
we put a lot of emphasize on being environmentally friendly (not just compatible),
to encourage the &quot;creativity of nature and of people.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<STRONG>Programme:</STRONG><BR>
<BR>
The workshop will deal with one case study: <BR>
<BR>
Preparing a small city for the Information Society (Visselh&ouml;vede in
the middle between the three big cities Hannover, Hamburg and Bremen)<BR>
<BR>
This is a case study based on very active citizen involvement, combining
using new economic opportunities with very good ecological restoration and
a very attractive landscape design.<BR>
<BR>
The case study is taking into account the development of new challenges
from the transition to the Information Society.<BR>
<BR>
The work in Visselh&ouml;vede is organized in five Citizens groups of a
total of about 100 people, with the backing of all political parties, the
administration, the economy etc.<BR>
<BR>
We have developed many new suggestions for the people and the economy taking
into account the paradigm shifts in ecology, economy, urban planning etc.<BR>
<BR>
The workshop in Amsterdam is organized starting with a presentation of the
experiences from the case study, with increasing time devoted to discussion
with work together without formal presentations in the last 90 minutes to
get recommendations and conclusions 
<PRE>
Friday, August 23

9.30 - 11.00	Presentation of the problems of Visselh&ouml;vede, paradigm
		shifts, background information, education of people:
		Wolf Dieter Grossmann and Mayor Radeloff (Mayor of 
		Visselh&ouml;vede)

11.00 - 11.30	Coffee break

11.30 - 13.00

Tools for planning in the new paradigm: Hans Dieter Kasperidus
Results from consultation with companies, tourist group and farmers
in the city of Visselh&ouml;vede: Michael Meiss

Discussion of about 30 minutes of all issues 

13.00 - 14.30	Lunch break

14.30 - 16.00

Using the ideas of Cross Catalysis Systems (related to Hypercycles) 
to understand the paradigm shift in economies and societies: Stefan
Fr&auml;nzle

Participation of citizens, companies and the administration and 
political parties: the motives behind the workshops organized in 
Visselh&ouml;vede: Wolf Grossmann

Discussion of about 30 minutes of all issues. 

Preparation of work together

16.00 - 16.30 Coffee break

16.30 - 18.00 Work with the workshop participants, conclusions, 
		summary

In addition the following paper has been accepted for presentation:
Jan Juffermans, De Kleine Aarde (<A HREF="ws33/juffermans.html">abstract</A>)</PRE>
<BR>
