<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Configuring Netscape</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>HOW TO CONFIGURE NETSCAPE WHEN FETCHING ACROBAT READER (PDF) FILES</H2>
1. Open up the Helpers preference in the Options meny.<BR>
<BR>
2. Lock fore Mime type/Subtype with the name application/pdf. If this Mime
type/Subtype does not exist make a new one of this type.<BR>
<BR>
3. Set Extensions to pdf.<BR>
<BR>
4. Set Application to your Acrobat Reader application by &quot;Browsing&quot;
for it.<BR>
<BR>
5. Set File type to PDF.<BR>
<BR>
6. Set Action to Launch application if you want Acrobat Reader to launch
automatically or Save if you want to save the file as a pdf document for
later viewing. Note, that if you use Launch application you will have to
save the document manually if you want to keep it.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
