<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Wals abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Agro-ecological studies at the university</H3>
Vida RutkovieneRutkoviene, V.<BR>
Associate professor, head of Ecology Department<BR>
Lithuaninan Academy of Agriculture<BR>
4324 Kaunas - Akademija, Lithuania <BR>
TEL: +7 370 7 296844, FAX: +7 370 7 296531, <BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:miskai@nora.lzua.lt">miskai@nora.lzua.lt</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Environmental problems have become so widespread that they can no<BR>
longer be ignored, neither in Lithuania nor globally.<BR>
<BR>
Lack of environmental knowledge and ignorance of natural objectives is<BR>
one of the reasons that causes the critical environmental situation. An<BR>
ecologically sound society based on sustainable development of<BR>
environmental education must become a guideline for humanity and first of<BR>
all for graduates from the different fields of sciences.<BR>
<BR>
The total system of agro-environmental education at the Lithuanian<BR>
Academy of agriculture will be presented. The ecology of activities<BR>
in Agriculture, Forestry and Water Management and their ecological<BR>
impacts on the wider environment form the core of studies.<BR>
Environmental education in the Academy is an appropriate level for<BR>
dealing with the sustainable agriculture problems of today and<BR>
future.<BR>
<BR>
