<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Industry and sustainability (Resources)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>2.3.A Industry and sustainability: Pioneer Industries on Sustainable
Renewable Resources</H2>
<BR>
Organised by the <A HREF="http://unep.frw.uva.nl/">UNEP-Working Group on
Sustainable Product Development</A>.<BR>
<BR>
<B>Convenors: <BR>
<BR>
</B>Hamed El-Mously<BR>
1 El - Sarayat Str., Abdou Pasha Sq., Abassiah, Cairo, Egypt<BR>
TEL/FAX: +20 2 284 2472<BR>
<BR>
Jorn Behage (Netherlands), UNEP-WG-SPD<BR>
<BR>
Topic: exploration of research and application of integrated use of renewable
resources, in relation to development<BR>
<BR>
<B>Programme</B>: 
<PRE>Friday, Aug, 23, 1996, 9.30 to 13.00

1. Opening Session (9.30 -- 11.00)

* Welcome from UNEP - WG - SPD Organizers
	(Hans  van  Weenon, Yorick  Benjamin, Anne Elsen or other
 	suggested names) (15 Min.)
* Keynote Address on  UNEP - WG - SPD Research Programme
  	Dr. Yorick Benjamin (20 Min.)
* Discussion (15  Min.)
* Keynote Address
	A Suggested Framework for Renewable Materials Resources
	Research: Challenges and Future Prospects.
	Prof Dr. Hamed El - Mously (20 Min.)
* Discussion (20 Min.)

2. Coffee Break (11.00 -- 11.30)
 
3. First Technical Session (11.30 -- 13.00)
Biopolymers from Renewable Resources and Fields of Application

* Highlights on Accumulated Experience in Use of Polymers,
	Coated Paper and Foil and Fortified Fibers in Different Fields
	of Application.
	Mr. Jorn E. Behage, The Netherlands.
* Development of Polylactic Acid Materials with Properties
	as Thermoplastics.
	Mr. J. F. Laim Boeck, The Netherlands

4. Lunch (13.00 -- 14.30)


Friday, Aug. 23, 1996, 14.30 to 18.00

1. Second Technical Session (14.30 -- 16.00)
Applications in Use of Renewable as Substitute for Non-Renewable
Resources

* Status of Research and Development on the Replacement  of
	Conventional  Plastics  by  Agricultural Waste Using Injection
	Moulding.
	Mr. Robert Wimmer, Austria
* Nigerian Experience in use  of  Wood  Waste  in  Manufacture  of
	Building  Materials  as  a  Substitute for Non-Renewable
	Materials.
	S.OO. Badejo, Nigeria.
* Environmental Issues in Jute Processing
	Dr. N.C. Som, India

2. Coffee Break (16.00 -- 16.30)
 
3. Third Technical Session (16.30 -- 18.00)
Future Prospects of Lignocellulosic Panel Production

* New Technologies and Research Opportunities of Panel
	Production from Renewable / Recycled Materials
	Prof. Dr. lng. E. Roffael , Germany.
* A Discussion on Use of Agricultural Residues in  Composition
	Panels.
	Prof. Dr. Hamed El - Mously, Egypt.


Saturday, Aug. 24, 1996, 9.30 to 13.00

1. Fourth Technical Session (9.30 -- 11.00)
Prospects of Use of Bamboo, Rattan and Palm Midribs as Substitutes for Wood

* Present  Status  of  Research   and   Development   Activities
	in the Area of Use of Bamboo as an Industrial Raw  Material.
	Associate Prof. Hong Jian Zhang , C'hina .
* Priority  Areas  of  Research  and  Development  on  the
Processing and Utilisation of Rattan
	Dr. Abd Latif Mohmod , Malaysia
* Achievements-to-Date and  Future Prospects of  Research on Use
	 of Date Palm Leaves' Midribs as a Substitute for Sawn Wood.
	Prof. Dr. Hamed El - Mously, Egypt.

2. Coffee Break (11.00 -- 11.30)

3. General Session (11.30 -- 13.00)

* Discussion of Research Policies and Proposal of New Research Programmes.
* Comments made by representatives of invited funding agencies
* Farewell words ( Hans van Weenen, Yorick Benjamin, Anne Elsen or other
suggested names.</PRE>
