<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Juffermans abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Sustainable lifestyles and the role of local authorities<BR>
-- or: living in attractive eco-cities, <BR>
-- or: 'Think globally, Act locally'</H3>
Jan Juffermans<BR>
De Kleine Aarde<BR>
Het Klaverblad 1, P.B. 151, 5280 AD Boxtel, Nederland<BR>
TEL: +31 411 68 4921, FAX: +31 411 68 3407<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Elements in the presentation:<BR>
&#183;Sustainable development is more than environment<BR>
&#183;Growing cooperation between local groups and municipalities<BR>
&#183;The 'Triade Model' for change<BR>
&#183;The Climate Alliance<BR>
&#183;The Rio Conference and 'Agenda 21'<BR>
&#183;The important role of municipalities - chapter 28<BR>
&#183;The 'Local Agenda 21'<BR>
&#183;Global aspects of local policy and lifestyles<BR>
&#183;Various (inter)national campaigns<BR>
&#183;The positive competition has started<BR>
&#183;The eco-city exists already<BR>
&#183;The importance of monitoring<BR>
&#183;Think globally, act locally<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
