<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Golubov abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>The ecological outcomes of the underground nuclear explosions and problems
of sustainable development</H3>
Boris Golubov<BR>
Russian Academy of Sciences<BR>
Scientific Secretary Scientific Council on the Problems of the Biosphere<BR>
Narofominskaya st. 2, fl 85, 119619 Moskwa, Rossia<BR>
TEL: +7 095 439 2448, +7 095 124 5388, FAX: +7 095 230 2090<BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:antip@ginran.msk.su">antip@ginran.msk.su</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
1550 underground nuclear explosions (UNE) for the military or<BR>
industrial purposes took place in 90 regions of the globe. Each UNE is <BR>
accompanied by a large number of the primary processes in the earth crust
that stimulate<BR>
secondary processes which influence on the landscapes and biosphere may
be<BR>
realized bit by bit on enormous area after UNE during ten or more <BR>
years. The primary processes falls into nuclear fission, hydrodynamic and
quasi-static<BR>
phases characterized by the special features of the radiation, physical,<BR>
mechanical, and chemical effects near UNE locality. The secondary <BR>
processes include the phases of the arch collapse, after shocks and strain
relaxation.<BR>
The investigations of many FSU UNE locations and data<BR>
generalization about UNE in USA and other countries make it possible to
affirm development<BR>
of the regular series of the dangerous ecological UNE outcomes, for <BR>
example, catastrophic rock slides and rock massive deformations,disturbances
of the<BR>
fluid system regime, appearances of the repeated seismity and tectonic waves<BR>
running with the velocity near 60 km/year on a distance more 1000 km. As
a<BR>
result the radioactive contamination area is expanded, especially on the
oil<BR>
deposits exploring with the UNE technology, reability of the <BR>
depth exploration and industrial complexes is destroying etc.<BR>
<BR>
The most striking example is emergency reduction and irrigation of 15<BR>
underground gas-condense reservoirs on Astrakhan deposit in 1986. The<BR>
reservoirs were constructed in 1980-1984 with the aid of UNE in <BR>
the salt range on the depth near 1 km. The same emergency situation with
radioactive<BR>
contamination of landscapes was revealed on Osinsk and Gezh oil deposits
in<BR>
the Perm region. UNE were used in order to increase the oil extraction<BR>
here. The immunity and blood systems affects of the many peoples, who was
working on <BR>
that oil deposits more than five years, are established.<BR>
<BR>
The incontrovertible proofs of extremely high Pu-239,240 concentration<BR>
in soils, vegetation and alive organisms are obtained for the number <BR>
UNE locality in Yakutua.<BR>
<BR>
On the one hand the problem of the UNE ecological outcomes is vital<BR>
question for the nuclear-weapon states: FSU, USA, France,<BR>
Great Britain, China and India. For them the removal or risk reduction of
the dangerous <BR>
UNE outcomes includes steps such as:<BR>
&#183;investigations of the primary UNE-processes on the<BR>
basis of the official information about UNE parameters and <BR>
geological structures;<BR>
&#183;data collection and monitoring on the secondary processes<BR>
development in order to evaluate the state and radioactive contamination
of<BR>
the natural and industrial complexes in the UNE environs;<BR>
&#183;biological and medical<BR>
examinations on the radioactive and chemical affects of the <BR>
UNE-industrial technologies on the alive organisms;<BR>
&#183;the definition of the economic,<BR>
technical and organization means for the sustainable development in the
<BR>
UNE regions.<BR>
<BR>
On the other hand above-mentioned problem is a matter of great concern<BR>
for the world as a whole because of two reasons. Firstly the elimination
of<BR>
chemical, nuclear and biological weapons strategy intend put into practice
<BR>
UNE technology and so is connected with the Nuclear-Weapon-Free World problem.<BR>
Secondly the theoretical modelling indicate that geodynamic UNE <BR>
effects may exercise influence on the own frequency oscillation on the Earth
and so may<BR>
reveal new aspects of the global ecological security.<BR>
<BR>
<HR>Go back to the <A HREF="../ws42nucwea.html#anchor515837">workshop 4,2</A><A HREF="../ws35polsus.html#anchor10311622">
</A>page.<BR>
