<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Vogt abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Possibilities of the civilian reuse of large military facilities</H3>
Roland Vogt<BR>
Department of Conversion, Ministry of Economy of the State of Brandenburg<BR>
Network Demilitarized<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Conditions for success and obstacles for conversion:<BR>
After five years of intensive engagement with conversion in the<BR>
State of Brandenburg and observations of efforts elsewhere, we note the<BR>
following:<BR>
<BR>
Conditions for successful conversion<BR>
<BR>
&#183;The understanding is needed that conversion is a high priority<BR>
political responsibility for shaping developments.<BR>
&#183;The conceptual basis needs to be created (e.g.&uuml;with<BR>
guidelines for conversion, as in the State of Brandenburg).<BR>
&#183;A positive climate and awareness for conversion must be achieved.<BR>
&#183;Coordinated inter-departmental approaches are needed.<BR>
&#183;The capacity for technical assistance and consultation needs to<BR>
be developed (e.g. the Advisory Handbook for Conversion and the<BR>
training of conversion experts.<BR>
&#183;Conversion has the Governor's attention.<BR>
&#183;Creation of especially attractive inducements for economic<BR>
activity and investments.<BR>
&#183;Daring and creative initiatives by those involved in conversion<BR>
processes.<BR>
&#183;Openness for a radical departure from previous uses of the <BR>
facilities and bases.<BR>
&#183;Mental preparedness for new ideas.<BR>
<BR>
Obstacles for conversion include:<BR>
<BR>
&#183;Underdeveloped awareness of priorities among relevant<BR>
decision-makers in business, government and the media.<BR>
(&quot;Conversion has no lobby.&quot;)<BR>
&#183;The limits to the public financing allocated to conversion<BR>
(especially by the federal government).<BR>
&#183;The lack of transparency of existing programs for financial<BR>
assistance (&quot;program jungle&quot;) and, with the exception of the<BR>
E.U. KONVER program, a lack of support instruments so <BR>
designed that they can address the specific tasks of conversion.<BR>
&#183;The lack of market demand for land in less favourable locations<BR>
in the face of the very large amount of competitively available land <BR>
of vacant industrial sites and unused open green spaces.<BR>
&#183;Unclear land titles.<BR>
&#183;Years and decades in which the military land was &quot;invisible&quot;<BR>
and blocked out of consideration for civilian community needs.<BR>
<BR>
<HR>Go back to the <A HREF="../ws44condis.html#anchor236576">workshop 4,4</A>
page.<BR>
