<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Blazejczak abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Changing industrial metabolism -- The case of heavy metal pollution</H3>
J&uuml;rgen Blazejczak<BR>
Deutsches Institut f&uuml;r Wirtschaftsforschung<BR>
K&ouml;nigin-Luise-Str. 5, 14191 Berlin, Deutschland<BR>
TEL: +49 30 89 789 359, FAX: +49 30 89 789 200, <BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:jblaze@diw-berlin.de">jblaze@diw-berlin.de</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The paper presents the methods, results and preliminary conclusions of a<BR>
study being undertaken at the International Institute for Applied<BR>
Systems Analysis (IIASA) as part of a project on `Regional Material<BR>
Balance Approaches to Long-Term Environmental Policy Planning'. This<BR>
study aims at a better understanding of policy options for dealing with<BR>
heavy metal pollution in Katowice - a highly industrialized and heavily<BR>
polluted region in Poland.  For this purpose it analyses policies in a<BR>
region where clean-up started 30 years ago - the Ruhr area in Germany<BR>
which historically shares many common features with Katowice.<BR>
<BR>
The study identifies key elements of Ruhr policies and evaluates them in<BR>
terms of effectiveness, costs, flexibility, etc. To determine the<BR>
effects of a transfer to Poland of elements which seem beneficial on the<BR>
basis of these criteria, local conditions in Katowice are thoroughly<BR>
analyzed. The development of new tools for environmental policy is being<BR>
taken into account.<BR>
<BR>
The study concludes that while traditional policies of the kind<BR>
implemented in the Ruhr have solved some of the worst problems, mostly<BR>
from large industrial sources, they have failed to tackle others less<BR>
suitable for regulation through standard measures. This applies to<BR>
emissions from diffuse sources as well as large contaminated areas like<BR>
agricultural land and allotment gardens. Thus there remains a need to<BR>
design instruments which create incentives for appropriate behavioural<BR>
changes of individuals.<BR>
<BR>
