<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Kiselev 2 abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Necessary conditions of existence and  development of  atomic power
in Russia<BR>
</H3>
Guennadi V. Kiselev<BR>
Head of the Reactor Department of the <BR>
State Scientific Center of the Russian Federation<BR>
Institute of Theoretical and Experimental Physics<BR>
B. Cheremuskinskaya 25, 117259 Moskwa , Rossia<BR>
TEL: +7 095 127 0558, <BR>
FAX: +7 095 127 0543, TEL/FAX: +7 095 930 6130 <BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:kiselev_g@vitep5.itep.ru">kiselev_g@vitep5.itep.ru</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
In report problems, worth before atomic power of Russia at the present<BR>
stage of its development with allowance for technical, ecological,<BR>
economic, social, political and defence factors are analyzed. On the<BR>
basis of this analysis are specified on such unsolved problems or the<BR>
decision of which claims the costs of significant funding such, as<BR>
increase of nuclear safety existing Nuclear Power Plants (NPP),<BR>
inefficient use of nuclear fuel in reactors VVER and RBMK,<BR>
decommissioning of NPPs, safe storage and management about nuclear fuel.<BR>
It is underlined a lot disadvantages in operation acting NPPs, in<BR>
particular, on absence of automated system of measurement of one of<BR>
important parameters of nuclear safety - operative margin of reactivity,<BR>
on disadvantage, connected with the compensation of the reactivity<BR>
changes by liquid absorber, on absence of passive systems of safety and<BR>
etc. It means that there is principle possibility for the power<BR>
excursion on prompt neutrons in connection with the error of personnel.<BR>
<BR>
The brief description of the Concept of development of atomic power in<BR>
Russia, federal program of the management with radioactive waste is<BR>
resulted. The list of numerous types of power reactors developed now in<BR>
Russia is presented. Estimation of efficiency for measures stipulated in<BR>
these programs is given. A problem of use weapon grade and power <BR>
plurinium in existing and advanced reactors as nuclear fuel is<BR>
discussed. Difficulties, connected with the realization of a closed<BR>
nuclear fuel cycle are considered.<BR>
<BR>
Necessary conditions for safe existence and further development of<BR>
atomic power of Russia are formulated. To this conditions is<BR>
concerned:<BR>
<UL>
  <LI>&#183;increase first of all of nuclear safety existing NPPs, in particularly,
development and maintenance all NPPs by automated systems of measurement
of an operative margin reactivity, continuation of activity on improvement
of systems of emergency protection etc.;
  <LI>&#183;increase of culture of safety at operation NPPs;
  <LI>&#183;a decommissioning NPPs of the first generation, safety which
not satisfied modern requests;
  <LI>&#183;acceleration of work on reduction of volume liquid radioactive
waste,
  <LI>stored on sites of NPPs and other objects nuclear Industry of Russia;
  <LI>&#183;development of advanced power reactors with improved parameters
on use of nuclear fuel and on increasing of thermal efficiency and safety;
  <LI>&#183;realization of system researches on optimization of a fuel cycle
of atomic power;
  <LI>&#183;strengthening of work on information of the population on work
of atomic power and enterprises of a nuclear fuel cycle; establishment special
payments for the population, living in regions with NPPs and the enterprises
of a nuclear fuel cycle;
  <LI>&#183;completion activity on preparation and issue of the laws in
the field of atomic energy.
</UL>
<BR>
<BR>
