<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Workshop: Gelman-Muravchik abstract</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<H2>Abstract</H2>
<H3>Disaster control and sustainable development</H3>
Ovsei Gelman-Muravchik<BR>
Instituto de Ingtenieria, UNAM<BR>
Programa Interinstitucional de Prevencion de Riesgo y Monitoreo Industrial<BR>
Universidad Nacional Aut&ograve;noma de M&eacute;xico<BR>
Ed. 12, Instituto de Igneria<BR>
Apdo.P. 70-472, Ciudad Universitaria, M&eacute;xico DF, 04510, M&eacute;xico<BR>
TEL: +52 5 622 8171 / 8132 till 37, <BR>
FAX: +52 5 622 8091<BR>
E-MAIL: <A HREF="mailto:ogm@pumas.iingen.unam.mx">ogm@pumas.iingen.unam.mx</A><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
The concept of Sustainable Development that initially emerged from the <BR>
problems of the non renewable resources over exploitation has became <BR>
related with more general problems of the Environment Protection and <BR>
Conservation, which absence, frequently, results in the substantial, <BR>
and sometimes irreversible alteration, of the ecological systems and <BR>
the relationships between them, what has been causing, due to their <BR>
fragility, their partial or complete destruction and, therefore, <BR>
the loss of the biodiversity.<BR>
<BR>
In this context it is important to take into account that the one of the
<BR>
main causes of the Ecological Disasters constitutes the Technological <BR>
Disaster that, in general terms, is defined like the product of the <BR>
inadequate operation of the technological means and industrial processes,
<BR>
due to the human errors and/or the equipment failures, because of their
<BR>
own wearing away or due to the impacts of destructive phenomenon. These
<BR>
alterations are able to, on one hand, provoke the decrease or even the <BR>
complete interruption of the operation of different subsistence systems,
<BR>
such as of electric power, of communications, of production, of drinkable
<BR>
water, of drainage, of transportation. On the other hand, the accident <BR>
produced by the equipment breakdown and the alteration of industrial <BR>
processes that are using the high risk activities and, in particular, <BR>
that are managing, this is, using, producing, storing, transporting, <BR>
distributing and discarding dangerous substances and energies<BR>
that could result in very serious and extensive impacts to the environment,
<BR>
due to their toxic, inflammable, explosive, oxidizing, radioactive and/or
<BR>
genotoxic characteristics.<BR>
<BR>
Due to the fact that the industrial processes are carried out in chemical
<BR>
reactors and are using electromechanical measuring devices, which are located
<BR>
in the buildings, all of them exposed and vulnerable to the adverse impacts,
<BR>
implies the necessity to study the dependence of Technological Disaster
from <BR>
the destructive phenomenon in order to realize the risk assessment and risk
<BR>
reduction.<BR>
<BR>
Moreover, the disasters, by themselves and due to their medium and long
term <BR>
consequences, are constituting a serious obstacle to the development of
any <BR>
country, because, besides of the costs that imply their attention and the
<BR>
consequent recovery, are interrupting the normal process of the development
<BR>
and are diminishing the achieved level of the population well-being.<BR>
<BR>
Thus a Sustainable Development could not be <BR>
reached if there have not been taken into account the <BR>
necessity of disaster control, such as its prevention and mitigation, <BR>
as well as the preparations in order to assist the emergency situations
<BR>
and to reduce the possible extension of the disaster.<BR>
<BR>
<HR><BR>
