<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>INES Congress: Zegras et al.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
The International Institute for Energy Conservation (IIEC) announces the<BR>
release of a new transportation document, Modeling Urban Transportation<BR>
Emissions and Energy Use: Lessons for the Developing World (By C. Zegras,
<BR>
D. Guruswamy, E. Miller, &amp; A. Tomazinis). <BR>
<BR>
The report attempts to assess the capabilities of urban transportation<BR>
demand forecasting, emissions, energy, and land-use models to meet the<BR>
needs of analysis in today's resource-constrained world. Drawing from<BR>
North American experiences, the report pro vides a brief history of<BR>
these models and explores their application, shortcomings, and<BR>
potentials. At the same time, the report examines the use of these<BR>
models in the diverse urban environments of the developing world,<BR>
analyzing applications to-date, m odel and data limitations, technical<BR>
capacity, and opportunities for future use. <BR>
<BR>
Directed at the policymaker and the layperson, the document is not<BR>
intended to be technical. Instead, it attempts to make the technical<BR>
more understandable to a broad audience, thereby facilitating a basic<BR>
understanding of modeling for urban transportati on energy and emissions<BR>
and promoting further research into the subject area. By evaluating<BR>
these models, the report aims to stimulate progress towards their more<BR>
effective use in both analyzing the feasibility of improving local urban<BR>
conditions as well as evaluating the possible role of urban<BR>
transportation options in offsetting greenhouse gas emissions. <BR>
<BR>
The report is available for $20.00 from IIEC (FREE to individuals from<BR>
developing countries) by check or money order mailed to IIEC's<BR>
Washington, D.C. office:<BR>
<BR>
IIEC- Publications<BR>
750 First Street, N.E. <BR>
Suite <BR>
940 Washington, D.C. 20002 USA <BR>
Phone: 202 842 3388 Fax: 202 842 1565<BR>
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:iiec@digex.net">iiec@digex.net</A><BR>
<BR>
<HR>Go back to the<A HREF="../littransp.html"> transportation litterature
page</A>.<BR>
<BR>
Go back to the <A HREF="../../../amsterdam">main conference page</A>.<BR>
