<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>OIE - File Downloads</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../image/back.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#6B9F00" VLINK="#006BB4" TEXT="#000000">

<TABLE>
<TR VALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><H1>File downloads</H1>
<TD><IMG SRC="../image/globe_p.gif"  BORDER=0>
</TABLE>

<P>The OIE develops and supports a number of software products relating to animal health.  Updates to programs or data are posted here as appropriate.
<BR><EM>All files placed on this server have been tested with a number of anti-virus products and are, to the best of our knowledge, free of viruses.
<BR>If you encounter any problems in downloading or using these products, please send a problem report to the OIE.</EM></P>
<BR>
<H2><A HREF="handi_a.htm"><STRONG>HandiSTATUS</STRONG></A></H2>
<P><STRONG>HandiSTATUS</STRONG> is  a computer application whose development is the result of collaboration between IICA, OIE, FAO and WHO and which is aimed at facilitating the exchange of animal health information between international organisations and their member countries. All the data in the central OIE database on the frequency of animal diseases and the control measures applied in Member Countries are integrated into HandiSTATUS together with the complete <EM><A HREF="../publicat/stand_a.htm#Code"> International Animal Health Code</A></EM>.</P>

<BR>
<H2><A HREF="biotek_a.htm"><STRONG>Biotech</STRONG></A></H2> 
<P>The OIE <STRONG>Veterinary Biotechnology Database</STRONG> replaces the previous hard-copy <EM>Veterinary Biotechnology Newsletter</EM> published annually from 1990 to 1994.</P>
<P>This database contains information, received by the OIE from 192 internationally 
renowned laboratories around the world, on the veterinary applications of research in 
biotechnology, especially in the following areas:</P>
<UL>
<LI><EM>diagnosis</EM> of animal diseases and characterisation of pathogens by the use of 
conventional and recombinant monoclonal antibodies, polymerase chain reaction and 
other nucleic acid techniques, immunoenzymatic techniques, genetically or synthetically 
altered antigens, etc.
<LI><EM>disease prevention</EM>, such as studies on pathogenesis and host resistance, genetically 
engineered vaccines, and transgenic animal technology.
</UL>

<HR>
Back to the <A HREF="../HOME.HTM">OIE home page</A><BR>
