<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>List of FMD free countries</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../image/back.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#6B9F00" VLINK="#006BB4" TEXT="#000000">
<TABLE>
<TR VALIGN=CENTER>
<TD><H1>List of FMD free Countries</H1>
<TD><IMG SRC="../image/globe_p.gif"  BORDER=0>
</TABLE>

<P><EM>Annotated: December 1996</EM></P>
<CENTER>RESOLUTION No. XII
<H4>Recognition of the foot and mouth disease status of Member Countries</H4>
</CENTER>
<P>CONSIDERING THAT<BR>
<OL>
<LI>During the 62nd General Session, the International Committee adopted Resolution IX, 'Countries and zones that may be considered as free from foot and mouth disease (FMD)',<BR><BR>
<LI>During the 63rd General Session, the International Committee adopted Resolutions XI and XII, 'Establishment of a list of foot and mouth disease free countries where vaccination is not practised', and 'Procedure for the recognition of the foot and mouth disease status of Member Countries',<BR><BR>
<LI>The Foot and Mouth Disease (FMD) and Other Epizootics Commission, in their September 1995 and January 1996 meetings, evaluated submissions by Delegates of Member Countries who considered that their countries or zones within their territories, had one of the FMD free categories described in Chapter 2.1.1 of the <EM>International Animal Health Code</EM>, and wished this status to be recognised,<BR><BR>
<LI>In accordance with the procedure approved by the International Committee, the Central Bureau sent lists to all Delegates of Member Countries naming those countries, and a zone within one country, which the Commission supported for recognition of their FMD free status according to Chapter 2.1.1 of the <EM>International Animal Health Code</EM>. No critical statements on the proposed listing were received,<BR><BR>
<LI>Information published by the OIE is derived from declarations made by the official Veterinary Services of Member Countries. The OIE is not responsible for inaccurate publication of country disease status based on inaccurate or incomplete information or changes in epidemiological status or other significant events which were not promptly reported to the Central Bureau subsequent to the time of declaration of freedom,
</OL></P>
<P>THE COMMITTEE<BR><BR>RESOLVES<BR><BR>
That the Director General publish in the <EM>Bulletin</EM> the following list of Member Countries as FMD free countries where vaccination is not practised, according to the provisions of Chapter 2.1.1 of the <EM>International Animal Health Code</EM>:</P>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR><TD>Australia</TD><TD>Austria</TD><TD>Belgium</TD><TD><STRONG>[Bulgaria]*</STRONG></TD><TD>Canada</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Chile</TD><TD>Costa Rica</TD><TD>Croatia</TD><TD>Cuba</TD><TD>Cyprus</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Czech Rep.</TD><TD>Denmark</TD><TD>Estonia</TD><TD>Finland</TD><TD>France</TD></TR>
<TR><TD><STRONG>[FRY (Serbia and Montenegro) <EM>1</EM>]*</STRONG></TD><TD>Germany</TD>
<TD><STRONG>[Greece]*</STRONG></TD><TD>Haiti</TD><TD>Honduras</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Hungary</TD><TD>Iceland</TD><TD>Indonesia</TD><TD>Ireland</TD><TD>Italy</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Japan</TD><TD>Korea</TD><TD>Lithuania</TD><TD>Luxembourg</TD><TD>Madagascar</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Malta</TD><TD>Mexico</TD><TD>Netherlands</TD><TD>New Caledonia</TD><TD>New Zealand</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Norway</TD><TD>Poland</TD><TD>Portugal</TD><TD>Romania</TD><TD>Singapore</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Slovakia</TD><TD>Slovenia</TD><TD>Spain</TD><TD>Sweden</TD><TD>Switzerland</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Taipei China</TD><TD>United Kingdom</TD><TD>United States of America</TD><TD>Uruguay</TD><TD></TD></TR></TABLE>
</CENTER>
<P>And<BR><BR>
That the Director General publish in the <EM>Bulletin</EM> the following Member Country as having an FMD free zone in which vaccination is not practised, according to the provisions of Chapter 2.1.1 of the <EM>International Animal Health Code</EM>:</P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR><TD>South Africa <STRONG><EM>2</EM></STRONG></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<BR><HR>
<EM><STRONG>1</STRONG>	Status of OIE membership to be clarified<BR><BR>
<STRONG>2</STRONG>	Zone designated by the Delegate of South Africa in documents addressed to the Director General of the OIE on 3 May and 18 December 1995<BR><BR>
<STRONG>*	[country]</STRONG>: countries between brackets have their FMD free status suspended due to recent occurrence of disease
</EM>
