<P><STRONG>
*<BR>*   *</P>
<A NAME="Sec4"></A><P>NEWCASTLE DISEASE IN THE NETHERLANDS<BR>The Delegate declares his country free</P>
</CENTER>
<P></STRONG>
See also <A HREF="A09_29.HTM#Sec4"> 2 August 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 29</A>, <A HREF="A09_24.HTM#Sec1"> 28 June 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 24</A>, <A HREF="A09_19.HTM#Sec7"> 24 May 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 19</A><P><EM>
Text of a communication received on 31 January 1997 from Dr C.C.J.M. van der Meijs, Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Nature Management and Fisheries, The Hague:</P>
<P></EM>
Follow-up report  No. 1</P>
<P>The last outbreak of Newcastle disease in the Netherlands occurred on 23 July 1996. No new outbreaks have occured since that date.</P>
<P>The Netherlands practises a stamping-out policy for Newcastle disease. This means that, under the terms of Article 2.1.15.2 of the OIE <EM>
International Animal Health Code</EM>
, the Netherlands may therefore be considered as free from Newcastle disease, with effect from 23 January 1997.</P>
</BODY>
