</EM>
Nordrhein-Westfalen <EM>
Land</EM>
.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Details concerning the outbreak:</P>
<CENTER></STRONG></EM><TABLE BORDER=2>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>No.
<TD>Species
<TD>No. of animals<BR>in the outbreak
<TD>No. of<BR>cases
<TD>No. of<BR>deaths
<TD>No. of animals destroyed
<TD>No. of animals slaughtered
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>1/97
<TD>bov
<TD>8
<TD>1
<TD>1
<TD>7
<TD>0
</TABLE>
</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning affected population: </STRONG>
</EM>
a cow of the Galloway breed, born in July 1992.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
diagnosis made by the Federal Research Centre for Virus Diseases of Animals, T&uuml;bingen, using histopathology and Western blot.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
maternal transmission cannot be excluded, as the infected cow originated from a Galloway cow imported from the United Kingdom in 1990.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date: </STRONG>
</EM>
the remaining 7 animals were slaughtered on 22 January 1997 and their carcases will be destroyed.</P>
