</TABLE><BR>
</CENTER><CENTER>
<P><STRONG>
<A NAME="Sec1"></A>NEWCASTLE DISEASE IN THE UNITED KINGDOM / GREAT BRITAIN</P>
</CENTER>
<P></STRONG>
See also <A HREF="A10_05.HTM#Sec1"> 31 January 1997; Vol. 10 - No. 5</A>, <A HREF="A10_02.HTM#Sec2"> 10 January 1997; Vol. 10 - No. 2</A>, <A HREF="A09_21.HTM#Sec6"> 7 June 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 21</A>, <A HREF="A09_19.HTM#Sec3"> 24 May 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 19</A><P><EM>
Synthesis of two faxes received on 10 and 14 January 1997 from Dr K.C. Meldrum, Chief Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Fisheries and Food, Surbiton:</P>
<P></EM>
Follow-up report No. 1</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Final date of previous report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
6 January 1997 (see <EM>
Disease Information</EM>
, <STRONG>
10 </STRONG>
[2], 4).</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Final date of this report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
14 January 1997.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Number of separate outbreaks identified so far: </STRONG>
</EM>
three (3) farms.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Geographical identification of the new outbreaks: </P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
2/97.	County of East Sussex</P>
<P>3/97.	Ross on Wye, county of Hereford and Worcester.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Details concerning the new outbreaks:</P>
<CENTER></STRONG></EM><TABLE BORDER=2>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>No.
<TD>Species
<TD>No. of animals<BR>in the outbreak
<TD>No. of<BR>cases
<TD>No. of<BR>deaths
<TD>No. of animals destroyed
<TD>No. of animals slaughtered
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>2/97
<TD>avi
<TD>...
<TD>...
<TD>...
<TD>...
<TD>...
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>3/97
<TD>avi
<TD>33,000
<TD>1,067
<TD>1,067
<TD>...
<TD>...
</TABLE>
</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning affected population:</P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
Outbreak No. 2/97: broiler rearing unit, male birds, kept indoors</P>
<P>Outbreak No. 3/97: turkeys for fattening, kept indoors.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Diagnosis:</P>
<P>A.	Conclusions to date concerning nature of agent: </STRONG>
</EM>
intracerebral pathogenicity index: 1.75 for outbreak No. 2/97 ; 1.95 for outbreak No. 3/97.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
B.	Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
the diagnosis (virus isolation) was made by the Central Veterinary Laboratory, Addlestone.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
Outbreak No. 2/97 is a primary outbreak. Retrospective isolation of virus from birds already destroyed for other reasons.</P>
<P>Outbreak No. 3/97: possible local spread from infected premises.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken during report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
stamping-out policy; quarantine measures and movement control inside the country.</P>
