Extract from a fax received on 14 November 1996 from Dr L. Celeda, Deputy Director of the State Veterinary Administration, Prague:</P>
<P></EM>
The outbreak of classical swine fever reported in Nemcicky, Breclav district (see <EM>
Disease Information</EM>
, <STRONG>
9 </STRONG>
[43], 165) is due to indirect transmission from wild boar (<EM>
Sus scrofa</EM>
).</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures: </STRONG>
</EM>
a serological screening programme is being continued in the protection and surveillance zones; reduction of wild boar population.</P>
