<A NAME="Sec1"></A>FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN AZERBAIJAN<BR>End of the outbreak</P>
</CENTER>
<P></STRONG>
See also <A HREF="A09_30.HTM#Sec1"> 9 August 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 30</A>, <A HREF="A09_12.HTM#Sec3"> 29 March 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 12</A>, <A HREF="A09_06.HTM#Sec3"> 16 February 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 6</A><P><EM>
Translation of a fax received on 12 October 1996 from Dr M. Gousejnov, Director of Veterinary Services, State Veterinary Committee, Baku:</P>
<P></EM>
S. R. - 2  No. 1</P>
<P>The foot and mouth disease outbreak reported on 21 July 1996 (see <EM>
Disease Information</EM>
, <STRONG>
9 </STRONG>
[30], 113) in the Sharur district, Nakhichevan Autonomous Region, was eliminated thanks to the measures applied. In consequence, the Republic of Azerbaijan may be considered free from foot and mouth disease of cattle and sheep with effect from 1 October 1996.</P>
