</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
clinical diagnosis was made on 26 September 1996. Samples were taken for laboratory tests (complement fixation and agar gel immunodiffusion tests). The sick animals had increased temperature, conjunctivitis, rhinitis and papules on the skin. </P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
epizootiological investigations are being carried out.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date: </STRONG>
</EM>
all affected and in-contact animals have been destroyed. The slaughter of small ruminants and trade in such animals and their products are prohibited. Strict police control measures have been applied in the outbreak. Clinical examinations are being carried out within the surrounding area.</P>
