<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Conclusions to date concerning nature of agent: </STRONG>
Chrysomyia bezziana</EM>
.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
the manner in which the screwworm fly entered the country is not yet known.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date: </P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
-	Movement of animals from or into the infested area was prohibited.</P>
<P>-	All infested animals were treated and kept under daily observation.</P>
<P>-	All livestock in, or adjacent to, high risk areas was treated with insecticide to reduce the risk of infestation.</P>
