</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease:</P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
-	In the Puy-de-D&ocirc;me department: outbreaks Nos. 2/96 and 3/96 were the result of contamination following trade with the establishment in outbreak No. 1/96.</P>
<P>-	In the Vaucluse department: infectious haematopoietic necrosis was suspected in a wild fish. The epidemiological survey confirmed the presence of the disease in the three fish farms on the river Sorgue.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date:</P>
<P></STRONG>
</EM>
-	Partial slaughter of susceptible animals in the affected fish farms. Destruction in a specialised facility. Salvage of some of the fish for human consumption.</P>
<P>-	Ban on the movement of susceptible animals within a zone around the farms. Tracing back and tracing forward.</P>
<CENTER>
