</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
during weekly clinical examinations for sheep pox in the village of Pastrogor, 18 clinically sick sheep were discovered in a flock having two owners. The animals had rhinitis, conjunctivitis and raised temperature, and erythematous plaques and papules on the head and belly.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
an epidemiological investigation is being carried out.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken during report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
the premises have been placed under strict quarantine. All affected and in-contact animals were immediately destroyed. Strict police control in Svilengrad district; trade and slaughter of sheep and goats in Haskovo region prohibited.</P>
