</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning affected population: </STRONG>
</EM>
slight drop in egg production and increase in white shelled eggs in a commercial table egg production unit comprising 25,200 layers in a single house. No other clinical signs.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
initial epidemiological investigations indicate that contact with feral pigeons may be the source. Investigations are ongoing.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
