<A NAME="Sec2"></A><P>NEWCASTLE DISEASE IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA</P>
<P>In psittacine birds</P>
</CENTER>
<P></STRONG>
See also <A HREF="A09_42.HTM#Sec4"> 31 October 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 42</A>, <A HREF="A09_35.HTM#Sec2"> 13 September 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 35</A>, <A HREF="A09_28.HTM#Sec4"> 26 July 1996; Vol. 9 - No. 28</A><P><EM>
Text of a fax received on 14 August 1996 from Dr L.J. King, Administrator, Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service, United States Department of Agriculture, Washington, DC:</P>
<P></EM>
S. R. - 2  No. 1</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Final date of previous report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
24 July 1996 (see <EM>
Disease Information</EM>
, <STRONG>
9 </STRONG>
[28], 107).</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Final date of this report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
12 August 1996.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
the following table summarises activities to date by State.</P>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=2>
<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>
