<A NAME="Sec6"></A><P>FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE IN ARMENIA</P>
</CENTER>
<P></STRONG>
<EM>
Text of a fax received on 8 August 1996 from Mr I. Martirossian, Deputy Minister of Food and Agriculture, Yerevan:</P>
<P><STRONG>
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: </STRONG>
</EM>
July 1996.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Geographical identification of the outbreak: </STRONG>
</EM>
north-western region.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
virus type O.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
the disease is believed to have been introduced from neighbouring countries.  Vaccination has prevented the spread of the disease.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken during report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
Existing stocks of 250,000 doses of vaccine and 350,000 doses imported from Russia are being used. However, it will only be possible to vaccinate 50% of the cattle population. Armenia needs 600,000 additional vaccine doses.</P>
<CENTER>
