<TR ALIGN=CENTER><TD>1  Primary outbreaks	2  Secondary outbreaks 	*  o/c = sheep + goats
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
<TD>
</TABLE>
</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Diagnosis:</P>
<P>A.	Nature of diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
outbreaks Nos 1/96 to 6/96: virus isolation by the OIE World Reference Laboratory for Foot and Mouth Disease (Pirbright, United Kingdom).</P>
<P>Outbreaks Nos 10/96, 12/96, 13/96, 15/96 and 16/96: clinical examination and/or epidemiological linkage.</P>
<P>Outbreaks Nos 7/96, 8/96, 9/96, 11/96 and 14/96: clinical signs. Confirmation from Pirbright Laboratory is pending.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
B.	Conclusions to date concerning nature of agent: </STRONG>
</EM>
on 25 July 1996, Pirbright Laboratory confirmed that the type O strain isolated from the delta area is genomically related to the recent outbreak strains from the Thrace region of Turkey, but not related to the strain isolated from Greece in 1994.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
despite the stringent control and safeguard measures taken, a second wave of outbreaks was reported in Evros in the last few days. Preliminary epidemiological investigations indicate that the primary outbreaks were caused by indirect contact with infected animals outside Greece, through movements of persons, or the watering of animals in the Evros river; the secondary outbreaks were caused by fomites, movements of persons or common grazing within Greece.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date: </STRONG>
</EM>
stamping-out/non-vaccination policy. In addition, the following measures have been in place since 4 July 1996 in order to prevent any further spread of the disease:</P>
<P>	preventive stamping out of all possible contact animals in the protection zones;</P>
<P>	census and registration of all herds of susceptible animals in Evros and regular, at least twice a week, clinical and epidemiological examination for foot and mouth disease;</P>
<P>	establishment of protection and surveillance zones around the outbreaks and a complete standstill on animals, products of animal origin and feedingstuffs inside these zones;</P>
<P>	ban on all movements of animals, products of animal origin and feedingstuffs within the entire Evros prefecture and strict police control measures on the Evros-Rodopi border. Disinfection of all vehicles leaving Evros;</P>
<P>	regular, at least once a week, clinical, epidemiological and, where appropriate, serological surveillance in the entire territory of Greece.</P>
<CENTER>
<P><STRONG>
*<BR>*   *</P>
