</EM>
two (2).</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Geographical identification of the outbreaks: </STRONG>
</EM>
State of Missouri:</P>
<P>1/96.	St. Louis</P>
<P>2/96.	Rolla.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments concerning affected population: </STRONG>
</EM>
psittacine birds. The situation is restricted to two aviaries. Neither commercial poultry nor wild/ornamental fowl are involved in this situation. </P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Diagnosis:</P>
<P>A.	Conclusions to date concerning nature of agent: </STRONG>
</EM>
velogenic viscerotropic virus.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
B.	Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
virus isolation was made at the National Veterinary Services Laboratories (NVSL), Ames, Iowa, on 16 July 1996.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
introduction of the disease appears to have been through the purchase of 16 pet birds from an apparent illegal importation (see table). No clinical disease has been observed since 5 July 1996, and there are no commercial poultry operations on or near the affected premises. An early response team is on site, and epidemiological investigations thus far indicate no evidence of spread. Epidemiological trace backs are still continuing.</P>
