<P><STRONG>
<EM>
B.	Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
clinical signs were observed in a few non vaccinated pigeons.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
introduction most likely through the purchase of (subclinically) infected ornamental pigeons at a small animal market. </P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken to date: </STRONG>
</EM>
stamping out of all birds, i.e. pigeons, geese and chickens. Cleansing and disinfection in and around the outbreak; tracing back.</P>
