</CENTER><STRONG><EM><P>Comments concerning affected population: </STRONG>
</EM>
all outbreaks occurred in small rabbit farms.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments concerning diagnosis: </STRONG>
</EM>
haemagglutination test using human type O red blood cells carried out in the Virology Section of the Central Veterinary Laboratory.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Comments to date concerning epidemiology of the disease: </STRONG>
</EM>
investigations into the cause of the outbreaks are continuing.</P>
<P><STRONG>
<EM>
Control measures taken during report period: </STRONG>
</EM>
movement restrictions were imposed on all infected farms. The Department of Veterinary Services has been supplied with an inactivated virus vaccine which is used all over the island to control the disease. A ministerial order has been issued. Disinfection of infected premises and control of rodents, wild birds and insects on infected farms.</P>
